.TH LPF-EXPLAIN 8 "June 2026" "lpf 0.2.0" "lpf Manual"
.SH NAME
lpf\-explain \- explain why a hypothetical packet passes or drops
.SH SYNOPSIS
lpf explain [\-\-json] [in|on <iface>] [from <addr>] [to <addr>] [proto <proto>] [port <port>] <policy>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Explain how a hypothetical packet would be handled by the policy.
The static evaluator simulates matching across rules, NAT, and redirect sections.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\-\-json
emit machine\-readable explanation JSON
.TP
in|on <iface>
hypothetical ingress interface (default: eth0)
.TP
from <addr>
hypothetical source address (default: 0.0.0.0)
.TP
to <addr>
hypothetical destination address (default: 0.0.0.0)
.TP
proto <proto>
hypothetical protocol (default: any)
.TP
port <port>
hypothetical destination port
.SH EXAMPLES
lpf explain from 10.0.0.5 to 1.1.1.1 proto tcp port 443 /etc/lpf.conf
lpf explain in wan from 203.0.113.10 to firewall port 22 /etc/lpf.conf
lpf explain \-\-json from 10.0.0.5 to 1.1.1.1 proto tcp port 443 /etc/lpf.conf
.SH FILES
/etc/lpf.conf
/var/lib/lpf/history
/var/lib/lpf/rollback
.SH SAFETY NOTES
This command is read\-only and does not inspect host state.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success.
Non\-zero when validation, planning, or host operations fail.
.SH SEE ALSO
lpf\-check(8), lpf.conf(5)
